  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preventing Forced Labour and Countering Irregular Migration in the Russian Federation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at supporting the Government of the Russian Federation in countering irregular employment, forced labour and human trafficking among migrants, while addressing the needs and vulnerabilities of the most vulnerable ones. The project&apos;s objective is two-fold. It will review and update the policy standards in the area of regular migration and employment thus reaching the outcome of improved evidence-based migration policy promoting regular migration channels, regular employment and managed recruitment of migrant workers in CIS and EEU member-states. It will address the needs of migrants, stranded due to mobility restrictions imposed to contain the spread of COVID-19 within the outcome to mitigate the risks and vulnerabilities of migrants associated with forced labour and human trafficking, as well as COVID-19.</narrative>
  </description>
